{{update|date=September 2018}}
[[File:Kanukoka.jpg|thumb|KANUKOKA is headquartered in the [[Nuuk Centrum]].]]

'''KANUKOKA''' ({{lang-kl|Kalaallit Nunaanni Kommunit Kattuffiat}}, {{lang-da|De Grønlandske Kommuners Landsforening}}) is the national association of [[Greenland]]'s municipalities, led by Palle Jeremiassen.<ref name="reform">{{cite news |url=http://sermitsiaq.ag/kanukokas-bestyrelse-konstitueret |title=Kanukokas bestyrelse har nu konstitueret sig |work=[[Sermitsiaq (newspaper)|Sermitsiaq]] |date=15 April 2015 |language=Danish |accessdate=15 April 2015}}</ref> The name is an [[acronym]] formed from the first two letters of each of the constituent words of the organization's name in the [[Greenlandic language]].

The aim of the organization is to facilitate cooperation between all four municipalities of Greenland: [[Kujalleq]], [[Qaasuitsup]], [[Qeqqata]], and [[Sermersooq]]. Based in [[Nuuk]], the organization runs the municipal elections every four years, with the last election taking place in 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kanukoka.gl/da/om_kommunerne/kommunalvalg_2008 |publisher=KANUKOKA, Official Website |title=Kommunalvalg 2008 |language=Danish |accessdate=9 July 2010}}</ref> All municipal authorities in Greenland are currently members of the organization.<ref name="about">{{cite web |url=http://www.kanukoka.gl/da/om_kanukoka/fakta_om_kanukoka/hvad_er_kanukoka |publisher=KANUKOKA, Official Website |language=Danish |title=Hvad er KANUKOKA? |accessdate=9 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721034806/http://www.kanukoka.gl/da/om_kanukoka/fakta_om_kanukoka/hvad_er_kanukoka |archivedate=21 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> The association is overseen by the Minister for Social Affairs in the Government of Greenland ({{lang-kl|Naalakkersuisut}}).<ref name="reform"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.nanoq.gl/emner/government/departments/ministry_of_social_affairs/minister.aspx |publisher=[[Government of Greenland]] |title=Minister for Social Affairs |accessdate=9 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728092340/http://uk.nanoq.gl/emner/government/departments/ministry_of_social_affairs/minister.aspx |archivedate=28 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> The annual [[budget]] of the association is 12.5 million [[Danish kroner]] (DKK), with the funds coming directly from municipal budgets.<ref name="budget">{{cite news |url=http://sermitsiaq.ag/politik/article111121.ece |title=Luk KANUKOKA |work=[[Sermitsiaq (newspaper)|Sermitsiaq]] |date=18 February 2010 |language=Danish |accessdate=11 July 2010}}</ref>

==History==
{{See also|Administrative divisions of Greenland}}
KANUKOKA was founded on 24 July 1972,<ref name="about"/> at which time there were 18 municipalities and 3 counties. After the administrative reform of 2008 was executed on 1 January 2009, there are four municipalities of Greenland, while the counties were discontinued. Two of the new municipalities—Qaasuitsup and Sermersooq—are the world's largest and second largest municipalities, in that order, with an area of {{convert|660000|km2|mi2|1|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.qaasuitsup.gl/da-DK/Om-kommunen/Fakta-om-kommunen |publisher=[[Qaasuitsup]] Municipality, Official Website |title=Fakta om kommunen |language=Danish |accessdate=16 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101030062742/http://www.qaasuitsup.gl/da-DK/Om-kommunen/Fakta-om-kommunen |archivedate=30 October 2010 |df= }}</ref> and {{convert|531900|km2|mi2|1|abbr=on}},<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sermersooq.gl/en/citizen/welcome_to_kommuneqarfik_sermersooq.aspx |publisher=[[Sermersooq]] Municipality, Official Website |title=Welcome to Kommuneqarfik Sermersooq |accessdate=16 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110218052852/http://www.sermersooq.gl/en/citizen/welcome_to_kommuneqarfik_sermersooq.aspx |archivedate=18 February 2011 |df= }}</ref> respectively.

==Future==
{{update section|date=May 2015}}
The formation of new municipalities brought new challenges to the association, with some of its tasks taken over by the new administrative entities with enlarged prerogatives.<ref name="scope">{{cite news |url=http://www.knr.gl/index.php?id=183&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=53593&cHash=64f89fb071 |title=Asii Narup: Kanukoka skal tilpasses nye tider |work=[[Kalaallit Nunaata Radioa]] |language=Danish |date=25 February 2010 |accessdate=11 July 2010}}</ref> In light of this extensive reduction of scope,<ref name="scope"/> the association is perceived as an expensive and redundant layer of [[bureaucracy]], hampering the direct cooperation between the municipalities and the government.<ref name="budget"/><ref name="completion">{{cite news |url=http://www.knr.gl/index.php?id=183&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=56262&cHash=0fcf47fd6e |title=Kanukoka drøfter fremtiden |work=[[Kalaallit Nunaata Radioa]] |language=Danish |date=19 May 2010 |accessdate=11 July 2010}}</ref> There is an ongoing discussion over its future, with a possible refocus from an independent organization to one being a vehicle for coordination of growth and development within the municipalities.<ref name="reform"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://sermitsiaq.gl/politik/article110528.ece |title=Vil forny KANUKOKA |work=[[Sermitsiaq (newspaper)|Sermitsiaq]] |date=11 February 2010 |language=Danish |accessdate=9 July 2010}}</ref> The proposed changes are part of the ongoing reform of the public sector in Greenland under the new government, in office following the [[Greenlandic parliamentary election, 2009|2009 parliamentary elections]].<ref name="reform"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dk.nanoq.gl/Emner/Landsstyre/Departementer/Landsstyreformandens%20Departement/Nyhedsforside/Nyheder_fra_dep_formand/2010/04/Kanukoka_dialog.aspx |publisher=[[Government of Greenland]] |title=Dialogen mellem Naalakkersuisut og KANUKOKA har kørt og kører upåklageligt |language=Danish |accessdate=9 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.nanoq.gl/emner/news/news_from_government/2010/02/speechsustainabledev.aspx |publisher=[[Government of Greenland]] |title=Sustainable Development in a Environmental perspective |accessdate=9 July 2010}}</ref> The reform is expected to be completed by 2013.<ref name="completion"/>

